body_html:
Ok I found the problem. I was on an outdated version of the mnist example. I had pushed a fix to the mnist example before the MNIST dataset fix to unsqueeze each image. After the MNIST dataset fix landed, this now resulted in images getting a 5th dimension, which is the cause of the error. I've updated the example so that it should now work (goldsborough/examples@9a74ef4)

Hope it'll now work.

body:
Ok I found the problem. I was on an outdated version of the mnist example. I had pushed a fix to the mnist example before the MNIST dataset fix to unsqueeze each image. After the MNIST dataset fix landed, this now resulted in images getting a 5th dimension, which is the cause of the error. I've updated the example so that it should now work (https://github.com/goldsborough/examples/commit/9a74ef4be3b1812f895ba2e2fe7a5ac9b1bdf07a)

Hope it'll now work.
